The wreckage of the plane of Steve Fosset, the billionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007 while flying over the Nevada desert, has been found.
The debris was found on a plateau at an altitude of 3,000 meters in the Sierra Nevada area of Mammonth Lakes, on the border between California and Nevada.
Inside the plane, no human remains, though.
Madera County Sheriff John Anderson has dispelled any remaining doubts: "The plane has been located, we have sent a team, and now we have confirmation that it is indeed the one that Steve Fosset was traveling on the day he disappeared", he said at a press conference.
The sheriff said no human remains were found on or near the plane.
In February, the 63-year-old billionaire was declared dead.
The US Transportation Safety Board (TSB) said that within hours of the wreckage being located, a team of investigators sent to the scene identified the aircraft as the Bellanca 8kcab, which disappeared on September 3, 2007, when Fosset took off from Yerington, Nevada on a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, still in California, not far from the Nevada border, some of Fosset's personal effects were found by a couple outside their Mammoth Lakes home.
There are two documents in Fosset's name, both issued by the Federal Aviation Administration of Illinois, cash and a sweater.
Fossett's search was stopped a month after she disappeared.
